hat ‘home’ can be a diasporic place, combining alienation with belonging. The volume also registers initial responses to the widened scope for Mansfield scholarship launched by the first two volumes of the new Edinburgh Collected Works of Katherine Mansfield.The volume includes:Previously unpublished poetry and fictionReports of current research findings on Katherine MansfieldAn introduction by Janet Wilson, Professor of English and Postcolonial Studies, University of NorthamptonReviews of recent publications on Mansfield and her contemporaries"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPostcolonialism in literature. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAretoulakis, Emmanouil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown-Berens, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColes, Gladys Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGasston, Aimee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrison, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIhimaera, Witi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Penelope, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKimber, Gerri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaddison, Isobel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagner, Brigid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMari, Lorenzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, W. Todd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMourant, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.